name: Book of Combos 1
description: An introductory text for first-time combiners. Improves your success rate.

name: Book of Combos 2
description: A basic text. Owning Book 1 and this improves your combining success rate.

name: Book of Combos 3
description: An intermediate text. Owning Books 1, 2 and this improves your combining success rate.

name: Book of Combos 4
description: An advanced text. Owning Books 1-3 and this improves your combining success rate.

name: Book of Combos 5
description: A pro-level text. Owning Books 1-4 and this improves your combining success rate.

name: Organizer Guide
description: An issue of Hunting Life magazine which explains how to maximize Item Box space.

name: Pack Rat Guide
description: An issue of Hunting Life magazine containing advanced item-cramming techniques.

name: Potion
description: Restores a small amount of Health. Try to combine these into something Mega-better!

name: Mega Potion
description: Restores a moderate amount of Health. This potion is a hunter's best friend.

name: Nutrients
description: Very slightly increases your maximum Health level.

name: Mega Nutrients
description: Slightly increases your maximum Health level.

name: Antidote
description: Removes all traces of poison from your system.

name: Immunizer
description: Boosts your natural ability to heal.

name: Dash Juice
description: Lets you run without tiring for a short period of time.

name: Mega Dash Juice
description: Lets you run without tiring for longer than with regular Dash Juice.

name: Demondrug
description: Boosts your Attack by filling you with -- guess what? -- demonic strength.

name: Mega Demondrug
description: Boosts your Attack even more than a regular Demondrug.

name: Might Pill
description: Temporarily endows you with the strength of a mighty god. Potent!

name: Armorskin
description: Boosts your Defense by turning your skin as hard as rock.

name: Mega Armorskin
description: Boosts your Defense even more than a regular Armorskin.

name: Adamant Pill
description: Temporarily makes your skin as hard as adamant. Potent!

name: Cool Drink
description: Provides temporary relief from extreme heat.

name: Hot Drink
description: Provides temporary relief from extreme cold.

name: Cleanser
description: Immediately removes any ice or mud on your body. Clean as a whistle!

name: Deodorant
description: An item that cures Stench. Releases a puff of deoderizing smoke when thrown down.

name: Psychoserum
description: Temporarily sharpens your sixth sense and attunes you to the ways of monsters.

name: Herbal Medicine
description: Removes all traces of poison and restores a slight amount of Health.

name: Max Potion
description: Fully restores Health and increases your maximum Health level all the way.

name: Ancient Potion
description: Fully restores Health and Stamina, and raises the max levels of both all the way,

name: Catalyst
description: Works with other materials to enhance their effects. Cannot be used by itself.

name: Energy Drink
description: This bottle is all you'll need to wake up! Shakes off sleep and restores Stamina.

name: Gunpowder
description: A dangerous substance that explodes when struck or heated.

name: Lifecrystals
description: Mysterious crystals long worshipped as a source of life.

name: Lifepowder
description: A Lifecrystal combination used as medicine. Heals with a single touch.

name: Dust of Life
description: A medicine with strone curative properties. Studied in secret, it is said to restore youth.

name: Tranquilizer
description: Medicine that works as an anesthetic when Combined.

name: Mystery Charm
description: A modest good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

name: Shining Charm
description: A curious good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

name: Timeworn Charm
description: A powerful good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

name: Powercharm
description: An amulet that raises Attack. Just carrying this gives you demonic strength.

name: Powertalon
description: A powerful amulet that raises Attack. Made with a Deviljho Talon.

name: Armorcharm
description: An amulet that raises Defense. Just carrying this hardens your skin like rock.

name: Armortalon
description: A powerful amulet that raises Defense. Made with a Deviljho Talon.

name: Raw Meat
description: Meat carved from a monster. Can be cooked, combined, or use to set a trap.

name: Poisoned Meat
description: Raw Meat that poisons whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

name: Tinged Meat
description: Raw Meat that paralyzes whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

name: Drugged Meat
description: Raw Meat that puts whatever eats it to sleep. Makes great bait for traps.

name: Rare Steak
description: Provides a small boost to your Stamina. This one's still red in the middle

name: Well-done Steak
description: Provides a moderate boost to your Stamina. Meat done right!

name: Burnt Meat
description: Meat that has been burnt to a crisp. It might boost your Stamina, or it might drain it ..

name: Chilled Meat
description: Meat that cools the body, wards off heat, and boosts a moderate amount of Stamina.

name: Hot Meat
description: Meat that warms the body, wards off the cold, and boosts a moderate amount of Stamina.

name: Boomerang
description: An usually-shaped weapon from abroad that returns to its user when thrown.

name: Throwing Knife
description: A standard throwing knife. Flies straight and true.

name: Poison Knife
description: A throwing knife with a venom-coated blade. Poisons targets.

name: Sleep Knife
description: A throwing knife whose blade has been dusted with sleeping agents.

name: Paralysis Knife
description: A throwing knife coated with toxins that paralyze a target.

name: Tranq Knife
description: A throwing knife used for capturing monsters ensnared in traps.

name: Bomb Casing
description: A base material for making hand-thrown bombs.

name: Paintball
description: Toss this scented paint at a monster to mark it, allowing you to track its position.

name: Flash Bomb
description: Flashes brightly on impact. Toss this right under a monster's nose to blind it.

name: Sonic Bomb
description: A grenade-like item that emits a high frequency blast of sound on detonation.

name: Dung
description: That's right: monster poop. The odor reveals too much about the monster's diet.

name: Dung Bomb
description: Releases an odor monsters find repulsive. It may even drive them away... or not.

name: Smoke Bomb
description: Creates a large cloud of smoke wherever it lands.

name: Farcaster
description: Instantly transports you back to base camp.

name: Tranq Bomb
description: A hand grenade used to capture monsters ensnared in traps.

name: Spider Web
description: A very sticky web.

name: Net
description: A sturdy net able to support a certain amount of weight without breaking.

name: Trap Tool
description: A tool you'll need to put a Pitfall Trap or other traps together with.

name: Pitfall Trap
description: Activates when something heavy walks across. Use this to capture monsters.

name: Shock Trap
description: Immobilizes a target. You can use this to capture monsters.

name: Small Barrel
description: How many whiffs does it take to find out what was in this empty barrel? Just one!

name: Large Barrel
description: How many licks does it take to find out what was in this empty barrel? Just one!

name: Barrel Bomb S
description: A small time bomb. You can use it underwater.

name: Barrel Bomb S+
description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb S. Small, but it packs a punch. You can use it underwater.

name: Barrel Bomb L
description: A potent bomb that detonates on impact. Waterproofed, so it still works underwater.

name: Barrel Bomb L+
description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb L. Deadly. Waterproofed, so it still works underwater.

name: Bounce Bomb
description: Buy from Store Clerk

name: Bounce Bomb+
description: An improved version of the Bounce Bomb. Requires some skill to use.

name: Felvine Bomb
description: Emits a scent Felynes love. Try hitting monsters with it.

name: Huskberry
description: A berry that is hollow on the inside.

name: Normal S Lv2
description: Non-specialized ammo. More powerful than Lv1.

name: Normal S Lv3
description: Non-specialized ammo that ricochets, resulting in high damage.

name: Pierce S Lv1
description: Armor-piercing ammo that deals multiple hits to some monsters.

name: Pierce S Lv2
description: Armor-piercing ammo. Higher-level ammo deals additional hits.

name: Pierce S Lv3
description: Armor-piercing ammo. This highest level deals the most hits.

name: Pellet S Lv1
description: Ammo that hits a wide area. Deals multiple hits at close range.

name: Pellet S Lv2
description: Ammo that hits a wide area. Higher-level ammo deals additional hits.

name: Pellet S Lv3
description: Ammo that hits a wide area. This highest level deals the most hits

name: Crag S Lv1
description: Powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

name: Crag S Lv2
description: Very powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

name: Crag S Lv3
description: Extremely powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

name: Clust S Lv1
description: Fragments into three shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

name: Clust S Lv2
description: Fragments into four shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

name: Clust S Lv3
description: Fragments into five shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

name: Flaming S
description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Fire.

name: Water S
description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Water.

name: Thunder S
description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Thunder.

name: Freeze S
description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Ice.

name: Dragon S
description: Mysterious ammo that won't work in regular Bowguns.

name: Poison S Lv1
description: Ammo dipped in poison. Some targets require multiple shots.

name: Poison S Lv2
description: Ammo dipped in deadly poison. Some targets require multiple shots.

name: Para S Lv1
description: Ammo that causes paralysis. Some targets require multiple shots.

name: Para S Lv2
description: Ammo that paralyzes quickly. Some targets require multiple shots.

name: Sleep S Lv1
description: Ammo containing a sleeping agent. Some targets require multiple shots.

name: Sleep S Lv2
description: Ammo packed with sleeping agents. Some targets require multiple shots.

name: Exhaust S Lv1
description: Special ammo that drains monsters' stamina.

name: Exhaust S Lv2
description: Enhanced special ammo that drains monsters' stamina.

name: Slicing S
description: Special ammo that ejects sharp blades on impact. Can it sever tails?

name: WyvernFire
description: Ammo patterned after Wyvern's Fire. Not as potent, but can be rapid-fired.

name: Recover S Lv1
description: Ammo that restores a small amount of Health to the target.

name: Recover S Lv2
description: Ammo that restores a moderate amount of Health to the target.

name: Demon S
description: Ammo that fills the target with savage amounts of strength.

name: Armor S
description: Ammo that hardens the skin, guarding against attacks and Wind Pressure.

name: Paint S
description: Ammo that marks a monster's position on your Map for a limited time.

name: Tranq S
description: Bowgun ammo used to capture monsters ensnared in traps.

name: Empty Phial
description: A regular old empty phial.

name: Power Coating
description: An arrow coating that increases the Attack of arrows fired. Capacity 50.

name: C.Range Coating
description: An arrow coating that increases close-range power and melee Sharpness. Capacity 20.

name: Poison Coating
description: An arrow coating that applies Poison effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

name: Para Coating
description: An arrow coating that applies Paralysis effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

name: Sleep Coating
description: An arrow coating that applies Sleep effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

name: Exhaust Coating
description: An arrow coating that causes arrows fired to drain monsters' stamina. Capacity 20

name: Paint Coating
description: An arrow coating that marks a monster's position on the map for a limited time. Capacity 99.

name: Worm
description: A fishing lure. Wriggles underwater, enticing those fishies to bite.

name: Mega Fishing Fly
description: A fishing lure. Causes a feeding frenzy. No fish can resist this one!

name: Frog
description: Know any monsters good at fishing? Try fighting fire with fire.

name: Sushifish Bait
description: A fishing lure with chum that makes Sushifish go, mmm.""

name: Burst Bait
description: A fishing lure with chum that makes fish that rupture upon death go mmm"."

name: Goldenfish Bait
description: A fishing lure with chum that makes Goldenfish go, mmm.""

name: Old Pickaxe
description: A cheap pickaxe with an easily nicked blade.

name: Iron Pickaxe
description: A pickaxe with a reasonably strong blade.

name: Mega Pickaxe
description: A pickaxe tempered with steel. This one won't nick easily.

name: Old Bug Net
description: A cheap net for catching bugs. It tears easily.

name: Bug Net
description: A durable net for catching bugs.

name: Mega Bug Net
description: An extremely durable net for catching bugs. This one is made to last.

name: BBQ Spit
description: Just what you need to cook meat. A must-have item for any hungry hunter.

name: Whetstone
description: A standard-sized Whetstone. Use it to restore a weapon's Sharpness.

name: Binoculars
description: Allow you to see farther and observe from a distance.

name: Garbage
description: Junk created when a combination attempt fails.

name: Field Horn
description: Used to attract certain monsters -- blow at your own risk. May break when used.

name: Health Horn
description: Restores Health to those who hear it. May break when used.

name: Antidote Horn
description: Eliminates poison in the blood of those who hear it. May break when used.

name: Demon Horn
description: Increases the strength of those who hear it. May break when used.

name: Armor Horn
description: Bolsters the defenses of those who hear it. May break when used.

name: Honey
description: Full of nutrients, but indigestible in this form.

name: Herb
description: Restores a very small amount of Health, but the flavor's not too hot.

name: Antidote Herb
description: A plant used in antidotes. It sometimes cures poison when eaten by itself.

name: Fire Herb
description: A wondrous, flammable plant.

name: Ivy
description: A vine of tough fibers. Woven, it is sturdy enough to hold a person's weight.

name: Sleep Herb
description: A plant containing sleeping agents.

name: Sap Plant
description: The sap it secretes is a strong adhesive. Careful you don't glue your Pouch shut!

name: Felvine
description: Melynxes' favorite food -- they just have to steal it.

name: Gloamgrass Bud
description: A night-blooming flower from a special herb native to Moga. It may have healing properties.

name: Hot Pepper
description: Blazingly spicy. Sure, it'll warm you up, but it's too hot to handle on its own.

name: Blue Mushroom
description: A well-known Combo material used to augment power. The deeper the blue, the better.

name: Nitroshroom
description: A hard-to-find mushroom with the power to generate blazing heat.

name: Parashroom
description: A mushroom that induces paralysis.

name: Toadstool
description: Logic says not to eat this poisonous fungus, but don't write it off completely.

name: Exciteshroom
description: This one has a very strange aroma... Edible? Only one way to find out.

name: Dragon Toadstool
description: A dangerous fungus said to suck the life out of the one who plucks it. Beware.

name: Paintberry
description: A berry with a shockng hue and an overwhelming scent. Look out: it WILL stain!

name: Might Seed
description: Temporarily raises your Attack when ingested by improving energy flow.

name: Adamant Seed
description: Temporarily raises your Defense when ingested by hardening tissue.

name: Nulberry
description: A mysterious berry that cures all elemental Blights (Fire, Water, Ice, Thunder, and Dragon)

name: Dragonfell Berry
description: Eat this to cure Dragonblight and temporarily increase Dragon Resistance.

name: Scatternut
description: A nut that violently ejects its contents when struck.

name: Needleberry
description: A berry covered with needle-like thorns.

name: Bomberry
description: A berry that explodes when struck.

name: Bumblepumpkin
description: A trendy orange pumpkin. If left undisturbed, it can grow to gigantic proportions.

name: Stone
description: A rock with just the right heft for throwing. Tried and tested!

name: Iron Ore
description: Ore with high iron content. Can be smelted and forged into various equipment.

name: Earth Crystal
description: Crystallized microbes which are prized as an abrasive when forging weapons.

name: Machalite Ore
description: An ore harder than iron, but also several times more difficult to forge with.

name: Dragonite Ore
description: An ore that yields metal superior to that of Machalite. Rare and valuable.

name: Lightcrystal
description: An extemely hard substance with a faint glow. Sometimes used for crafting tools.

name: Ice Crystal
description: Ice that will not melt at room temparatures. Can be used to create denser ore.

name: Firestone
description: Combusts even at room temperature. Its high heat can be used to fuse materials.

name: Carbalite Ore
description: An ore still being researched. It yields even better metal than Dragonite.

name: Fucium Ore
description: An ore composed of a mysterious metal, capable of fusing nearly any two materials together.

name: Eltalite Ore
description: A promising new ore that produces higher quality metal than Carbalite Ore.

name: Meldspar Ore
description: An ore composed of a durable, flexible metal that works well as a combining agent.

name: Firecell Stone
description: A magma-like deposit that only trained hands can properly work with.

name: Allfire Stone
description: An ore that blazes with an all-consuming flame. Requires considerable skill to mine.

name: Purecrystal
description: A crystal that's 100% pure. Hard enough to be used in workshop tools.

name: Armor Stone
description: Reacts uniquely to heat. Combine with other materials to create coating for armor.

name: Armor Sphere
description: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to armor to increase its strength.

name: Armor Sphere+
description: Fuse this high-quality Armor Sphere to existing armor to increase its strength.

name: Adv Armor Sphere
description: An advanced Armor Sphere. Rare in Moga Village. Save it for that special upgrade.

name: Whetfish
description: A fish with a dorsal fin hard enough to sharpen weapons with.

name: Sushifish
description: A fatty, delicious fish that restores a small amount of Health when consumed.

name: Sleepyfish
description: A fish that contains sleeping agents.

name: Pin Tuna
description: A fish with jaws covered in tiny, needle-like spikes.

name: Popfish
description: A fish that literally pops when it dies.

name: Scatterfish
description: A fish that dashes itself to pieces when it dies.

name: Burst Arowana
description: A fish that bursts open when it dies

name: Bomb Arowana
description: A fish that explodes when it dies.

name: Glutton Tuna
description: A fish that eats anything -- allowing you to sometimes get items from its stomach.

name: Small Goldenfish
description: A rare fish that commands a high price, but beware its ferocity, rookies!

name: Wanchovy
description: A fish that can induce exhaustion.

name: Blue Cutthroat
description: A fish that emits blue light. Its sharp body will cut you to pieces if you're not careful

name: Insect Husk
description: The remains of an insect. You must be one hardcore collector to hang onto this!

name: Stinkhopper
description: A grasshopper with a foul odor. Make fishing lures with it；its scent drives explosive fish wild.

name: Snakebee Larva
description: An unusual larva. Make fishing lures with it； its scent drives Goldenfish wild.

name: Godbug
description: An insect said to live 1000 years -- but no one's lived long enough to prove it.

name: Bitterbug
description: Boosts your natural ability to heal when eaten. It also cures poison... sometimes.

name: Flashbug
description: A nocturnal insect sometimes found in daylight. They emit a bright flash upon death.

name: Thunderbug
description: Releases an electric shock when struck. Used to light rooms and start fires.

name: Killer Beetle
description: This insect's hard shell is often used as an abrasive.

name: Hercudrome
description: Said to be the world's strongest bug. Used in forging, cooking, and more.

name: Fulgurbug
description: Thunderbugs which have been stimulated by Zinogre. They emit a pale blue light.

name: Rare Scarab
description: A rare and valuable insect that greatly assists in the bonding of metals.

name: Emperor Hopper
description: A grasshopper with an exceptionally strong shell. Prized as a crafting material.

name: Flutterfly
description: A butterfly with shimmering wings. So rarely seen in the wild, many believe it to be a myth.

name: Butterfly Beetle
description: A strange insect with the large jaws of a beetle and the delicate wings of a butterfly.

name: Monster Bone S
description: A handy material used to make everything from equipment to sundries.

name: Monster Bone M
description: A nicely-sized bone. Strong yet flexible, it's as reliable as steel and wood.

name: Monster Bone L
description: Wyvern bone needed to craft larger items. The right item will fuse this to a shell.

name: Mystery Bone
description: A weathered bone. Not sturdy enough to use in forging.

name: Unknown Skull
description: An animal skull worn and weathered beyond identification.

name: Monster Bone+
description: A top-quality monster bone. Hard to find, but vital for crafting powerful equipment.

name: Monster Keenbone
description: A rare bone with a razor-sharp tip that retains its strength even when crafted.

name: Monster Hardbone
description: A precious bone rarely yielded by large wyverns. Difficult to forge, but prized for its strength.

name: Monster Slogbone
description: An incredibly strong bone harvested from a fearsome wyvern. Its heft is impressive.

name: Avian Finebone
description: A bone from a Jaggi or other bird wyvern. Small in size, but high in quality.

name: Avian Stoutbone
description: The robust bone of a bird wyvern. Durable and easy to craft with this.

name: Jumbo Bone
description: A large, thick bone. Often cut apart in workshops for use in crafting.

name: Stoutbone
description: The large, sturdy bone of a beast. Prized by blacksmiths as a prime forging material.

name: Massive Bone
description: An impossibly hard bone from a large beast. It exceeds all known standards for crafting material.

name: Dragonbone Relic
description: A curiously unfossilized bone from a dragon that once roamed these lands.

name: Wyvern Fang
description: Used in Bowgun bullet points. Gunpowder shatters them, generating shrapnel.

name: Wyvern Claw
description: Used in Bowgun bullet points. Gunpowder triggers a blast with a wide radius.

name: Bird Wyvern Gem
description: A valuable gem that can be harvested from Jaggi and other bird wyverns.

name: Fey Wyvern Gem
description: An exceptionally pure gem taken from a bird wyvern. Its fragility makes it difficult to carve.

name: Poison Sac
description: A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.

name: Toxin Sac
description: A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.

name: Paralysis Sac
description: A monster organ that contains paralyzing neurotoxins.

name: Omniplegia Sac
description: A monster organ filled with potent neurotoxins. A single touch can cause paralysis.

name: Sleep Sac
description: A monster organ that contains a knockout powder capable of inducing sleep.

name: Coma Sac
description: A monster organ that contains dangerous powder. One whiff can induce a coma.

name: Flame Sac
description: A monster organ filled with flammable powder. Handle with caution.

name: Inferno Sac
description: A monster organ filled with powder that ignites if it so much as touches air. Danger!

name: Conflagrant Sac
description: A monster organ filled with a highly explosive powder. Extremely dangerous!

name: Thunder Sac
description: A monster organ that can store up large amounts of high-voltage electricity.

name: Lightning Sac
description: A monster organ that can store electricity as strong as lightning. It rumbles like thunder.

name: Frost Sac
description: A monster organ that contains a sub-zero liquid. Handle with extreme care.

name: Freezer Sac
description: A monster organ with tremendous freezing power.

name: Cryo Sac
description: A monster organ that has fierce freezing properties. It can coat an area in ice in a flash.

name: Aqua Sac
description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve water.

name: Torrent Sac
description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve copious amounts of water.

name: Flood Sac
description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve tremendous amounts of water.

name: Dash Extract
description: A mysterious substance that can be culled from certain monsters.

name: Pale Extract
description: Has the ability to amplify the effects of certain medicines.

name: Gargwa Feather
description: A big, beautiful feather plucked from a Gargwa. Often used as a fashion accessory.

name: Kelbi Horn
description: Infusions of powdered Kelbi Horn work wonders on tummyaches. It's a local secret!

name: Blue Kelbi Horn
description: An especially rare Kelbi Horn. Popular among traders.

name: Warm Pelt
description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

name: High-quality Pelt
description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

name: Prized Pelt
description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

name: Rhenoplos Shell
description: A very strong shell, considering it comes such a small monster.

name: Rhenoplos Scalp
description: A sturdy part of the skill that yields, shall we say, dashing results?

name: Rhenoplos Bone
description: As strong as it is heavy, this Rhenoplos bone is well-suited for use in crafting armor.

name: Slagtoth Hide+
description: Firm, lustrous hide often cut into large slabs. Prized for its water-resistant properties.

name: Bnahabra Shell
description: Every bit as sturdy as wyvern armor in the hands of a clever craftsman.

name: Bnahabra Wing
description: Difficult to forge with -- the results vary depending on which surface you use.

name: Altaroth Jaw
description: These durable mouthparts are surprisingly difficult to carve loose.

name: Altaroth Stomach
description: A transparent sac cut from an Altaroth's abdomen, used to store who knows what.

name: Crushing Fang
description: The strongest fang of a fanged beast. It can pierce a monsters's shell as if it were paper.

name: Jaggi Scale
description: A scale carved from a Jaggi. Not very valuable, but beginners can't be choosers.

name: Jaggi Scale+
description: A vividly-colored superior Jaggi scale that can be used to produce hardier equipment.

name: Jaggi Hide
description: Commonly used in this region. It can be made into any number of things.

name: Bird Wyvern Fang
description: A fang similar in value to the foreign Velociprey's. Used to make bowgun ammo.

name: G.Jaggi Hide
description: Durable, elegantly patterned hide from a Great Jaggi. Befits its position as pack leader.

name: G.Jaggi Hide+
description: The rugged hide of a strong Great Jaggi. Fewer wounds means higher quality and value.

name: G.Jaggi Claw
description: A hook-shaped claw cut from a Great Jaggi. Just like a Jaggi claw, only much, much larger.

name: G.Jaggi Claw+
description: A hook-shaped claw cut from a Great Jaggi. Well-Sharpened from countless battles.

name: King's Frill
description: Proof of who's boss among Jaggi -- and now proof you are on your way as a hunter.

name: Lagombi Pelt
description: A white pelt carved from a Lagombi. One touch and you'll be hooked on its soft, fluffy fur.

name: Lagombi Pelt+
description: A quality white Lagombi pelt. Its glossy, frosty shine makes it a sought-after luxury item.

name: Lagombi Fur
description: The very finest Lagombi fur, durable and yet surprisingly soft. A top-shelf item.

name: Lagombi Ear+
description: An impressive Lagombi ear. Highly-developed, it can become sharp as steel if polished.

name: Lagombi Auricle
description: A superior Lagombi ear with astonishing hearing capabilities. An exceptional crafting material.

name: Lagombi Plastron
description: A shell piece from a Lagombi's belly. Its ridges are what allow the Lagombi to slide on ice.

name: Lagombi Plastron+
description: A robust Lagombi Plastron. Strong, sticky and thick, it's used to make superior equipment.

name: Monster Fluid
description: Sticky fluid that is often found in insects after they feast.

name: Monster Broth
description: A broth made from only the thickest of a monster's juices. Quite rich.

name: Monster Essence
description: A broth made from only the thickest, choicest parts of a monster's juices. Gross?

name: Black Pearl
description: The Hunting Fleet sometimes brings these back. The black glow fetches a high price.

name: Rathian Scale
description: A scale from a flying wyvern native to this area. Rathian mate with male Rathalos.

name: Rathian Scale+
description: A fine Rathian scale. It may not look special, but its hardness puts other scales to shame.

name: Rathian Shard
description: A particularly thick Rathian scale. Its large size proves its owner's advanced age.

name: Rathian Shell
description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.

name: Rathian Carapace
description: A sturdy Rathian carapace. Even harder than a normal Rathian shell.

name: Rathian Cortex
description: A Rathian shell heavier than a carapace. Used to reinforce parts of equipment.

name: Rathian Webbing
description: Hard to forge with, but its thermal properties make it ideal for armor lining.

name: Rathian Spike
description: Needle-like hair found on the Rathian's back and wings. They contain poison.

name: Rathian Spike+
description: As sharp as the keenest blade. It is longer and sturdier than other spikes.

name: Rathian Surspike
description: Only a few of those superior spikes grow on a Rathian. It is both sharp and highly toxic.

name: Rathian Plate
description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

name: Rathian Ruby
description: A rare gem formed inside a Rathian. It seems almost too nice to forge with.

name: Rathian Mantle
description: A legendary Rathian scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

name: P.Rathian Scale+
description: A high-grade scale from a Pink Rathian. Chic hunters love the blend of strength and style.

name: P.Rathian Shard
description: A thick, shiny scale from a Pink Rathian. Rare is the artisan who has ever laid eyes on one.

name: P.Rathian Cortex
description: A hevy Pink Rathian cortex made up of a single beautiful plate. It commands top zenny when sold.

name: G.Rathian Shard
description: A thick Gold Rathian scale unlike anything seen before. Sunlight gives it an almost sacred glow.

name: G.Rathian Cortex
description: A cortex carved from a Gold Rathian. All who see it gasp at its intense glow.

name: G.Rath Surspike
description: A poisonous spike found on Gold Rathians in rare circumstances. It can pierce through anything.

name: Rathalos Scale
description: A Rathalos scale. Wyvern scales like this one and the harder shells are basic forging items.

name: Rathalos Scale+
description: An extraordinarily durable scale carved from the body of a Rathalos.

name: Rathalos Shard
description: A Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. Its strength is a natural wonder.

name: Rathalos Shell
description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.

name: Rathalos Carapace
description: A rigid Rathalos carapace. Even harder than a normal Rathalos Shell.

name: Rathalos Cortex
description: A robust Rathalos shell that is harder and sturdier than a carapace.

name: Rathalos Webbing
description: Hard to forge with, but its thermal properties make it ideal for armor lining.

name: Rathalos Wing
description: A wing that has been removed. Skilled artisans can craft it into strong equipment.

name: Rathalos Fellwing
description: A top-grade Rathalos wing, removed in full. Such majesty befits the King of the Skies.

name: Rathalos Tail
description: The severed tail of a Rathalos. It has any number of uses.

name: Rathalos Lash
description: A top-grade Rathalos tail. Strong ones like this are precious, and only used in select equipment.

name: Rathalos Plate
description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

name: Rathalos Ruby
description: A rare gem formed inside a Rathalos. It seems almost too nice to forge with.

name: Rathalos Mantle
description: A legendary Rathalos scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

name: A.Rathalos Shard
description: An Azure Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. It boasts beauty and strength.

name: A.Rathalos Tail
description: The severed tail of an Azure Rathalos. It fetches a high price due to its rarity.

name: A.Rathalos Lash
description: A top-grade Azure Rathalos tail. Strong ones like this are prized by all and sold at high prices.

name: A.Rathalos Wing
description: A wing that has been removed. Excellent for forging both weapons and armor.

name: S.Rathalos Shard
description: A Silver Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. Makes for a nice silver accessory.

name: S.Rath Cortex
description: A heavy Silver Rathalos cortex. This legendary item shines like moonlight, even in darkness.

name: Rath Marrow
description: Recent advances allow this marrow to be extracted. It ignites on air contact.

name: Rath Medulla
description: Recent advances allow this red hot organ to be removed, but it's hard to forge with.

name: Diablos Cortex
description: The rigid cortex of a Diablos, both harder and sturdier than its carapace.

name: Diablos Chine
description: Tough Diablos backplate, strengthened by burning sands. An ideal material for armor.

name: Diablos Hardhorn
description: An especially elegant Diablos horn with almost perfect shape. An extremely rare material.

name: B.Diablos Cortex
description: A heavy Black Diablos cortex. Its weight reveals its overwhelming density and strength.

name: B.Diablos Chine
description: Finely honed Black Diablos backplate. Best described as black, hard, and heavy.

name: Zinogre Carapace
description: The teal carapace of a Zinogre. Its magnificence reveals the futility of facing the monarch.

name: Zinogre Cortex
description: The teal cortex of a Zinogre. The monarch's armor crushes wills with its immense power.

name: Zinogre Horn+
description: A pointed Zinogre horn. When carved, it can be used to grant equipment incomparable power.

name: Zinogre Hardhorn
description: A mighty Zinogre horn. None can sand before its sky-shattering, awe-inspiring power.

name: Zinogre Claw+
description: A sharp, high voltage Zinogre claw. Its electrified attacks are truly brutal.

name: Zinogre Tail
description: The plate-covered tail of a Zinogre. It wields deadly force when swung.

name: Zinogre Lash
description: A superior Zinogre tail that wields incomparable destructive power.

name: Zinogre Shocker+
description: A Zinogre shell that stores and releases electricity. Grants a thunder god's power to gear.

name: Zinogre Jasper
description: A rare gem occasionally produced inside a Zinogre's body. The monarch's power swells within.

name: S.Zinogre Lash
description: A Stygian Zinogre's terrifyingly strong tail. Said to be able to slice through solid steel.

name: Dracophage Bug
description: Dragonfell Berry-loving bugs that store up Dragon energy. A Stygian Zinogre's power source

name: Brach Carapace
description: A hard Brachydios carapace. Glossy like obsidian, it adds a refined beauty to crafted gear.

name: Brach Cortex
description: The thick cortex of a Brachydios. Its stoic beauty adds strength and dignity to equipment.

name: Brach Ebonshell
description: An obsidian Brachydios brace. Makes especially strong armor, perhaps due to the slime mold.

name: Brach Ebonshell+
description: A premium Brachydios brace. The slime coating may contain weird bacteria, so be careful.

name: Brach Scalp
description: The large, protruding scalp of a Brachydios, covered in an explosive green substance.

name: Brach Scalp+
description: A hard and sharp scalp piece from a fierce Brachydios. Even more explosive than usual.

name: Mystery Slime
description: The explosive green substance found on Brachydios monsters. Handle with extreme care.

name: Glowing Slime
description: Highly explosive green slime found on a fierce Brachydios. Handle with extreme care.

name: Brach Pounder
description: A Brachydios arm that buried countless foolhardy hunters. It's covered in green slime.

name: Brach Pounder+
description: The arm of an especially angry Brachydios. Strong and heavy, as if made of iron.

name: Brach Pallium
description: A legendary Brachydios shell. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

name: Deviljho Scale
description: A greenish-black Deviljho scale. It's not often sold, as rumors claim it brings it misfortune.

name: Deviljho Shard
description: A heavy, high-quality Deviljho scale. Rumored to bring bad luck, but actually an excellent material.

name: Deviljho Hide
description: Black hide that is oddly slimy and difficult to forge with.

name: Deviljho Talon
description: A dangerously sharp, hooked talon. Inexperienced crafters risk serious injury.

name: Deviljho Ripper
description: An incredibly sharp, rigid talon. Even experienced handlers can be injured if not careful.

name: Deviljho Scalp
description: Removing this part of a Deviljho's skull releases an unimaginably putrid odor.

name: Deviljho Tail
description: A masive tail resembling a fin. Some folks are out to collect these exclusively.

name: Deviljho Flail
description: A large slab of a Deviljho's leech-like tail. Even so-called experts are shocked by it.

name: Deviljho Saliva
description: The symbol of a Deviljho's insatiable appetite. The strong acid corrodes all it touches.

name: Black Blood
description: Dark black blood characteristic of a Deviljho. It feels like it could jump up and attack at any time.

name: Vile Fang
description: A massive, overgrown fang that can chomp through anything. Filled with pure evil.

name: Deviljho Gem
description: A precious gem said to contain a Deviljho's might. Used in shady rituals.

name: Deviljho Crook
description: An unsettling scale that became warped as it absorbed the malice of the Deviljho's various prey.

name: Earth Dragongem
description: One of the tougher materials to get from a Jhen Mohran, and that's saying something.

name: Arzuros Shell
description: A shell piece from an Arzuros's head or back. Bends willingly and is easy to forge.

name: Arzuros Pelt
description: A pelt carved from an Arzuros. The white portion is soft, while the blue is short and taut.

name: Spongy Hide
description: Uncannily elastic hide that retains water quite well.

name: Vivid Feather
description: A superbly colored Qurupeo feather. Nothing less than a natural work of art.

name: Strange Beak
description: An oddly shaped beak. It's pleasant enough.

name: Barroth Shell
description: A Barroth's shell -- more often than not covered in mud, but strong either way.

name: Barroth Scalp
description: This durable part of the skull is also the hardest to remove.

name: Nibelsnarf Hide
description: Hide from a Nibelsnarf. Many are surprised by its bright colors, in contrast to the outer shell.

name: Vivid Fluid
description: A fluid which helps retain water in a Nibelsnarf and allows the beast to thrive in the desert.

name: Uragaan Marrow
description: Hard-to-obtain bone marrow used for special crafts as well as medicinal purposes.

name: Uragaan Scute
description: Even more heat resistant than the Shell, this is said to protect sensitive organs.

name: Duramboros Horn
description: The horn of a Duramboros. Wider than a man's chest；all who see it are rendered speechless.

name: Diablos Shell
description: This shell piece is dense, as one knock will tell you, and heavier than it looks.

name: Majestic Horn
description: A twisted Diablos horn in great shape. Use it to make more powerful weapons.

name: Gobul Hide+
description: Fine skin from a Gobul. Said to rejuvenate the skin, and quite popular with the ladies.

name: Gobul Spike+
description: A high-quality barb from a Gobul. Only stroner monsters have such well-shaped spikes.

name: Amber Tusks+
description: Amber tusks sharpened by countless kills. They can smash through gigantic ice blocks.

name: Barioth Pelt+
description: A high-quality white pelt with a lovely texture. Nobles use it as a symbol of authority.

name: Shell Shocker+
description: A superior shell found only on certain Lagiacrus. Its structure permits greater electric output.

name: Agnaktor Fin+
description: An Agnaktor fin with an elegant dappled pattern. Aparently a popular item with collectors.

name: Ceadeus Hide
description: Even for monster skin, this is remarkably solid. Takes time and effort to craft.

name: Crooked Horn
description: A giant horn that was formed over ages. It evinces all weight of history.

name: Luminous Organ
description: Who knows why this organ glows, but it seems to hold incredible power.

name: Alatreon Plate
description: This particular Alatreon scale grows in backwards. It is as sharp as a blade.

name: Alatreon Webbing
description: At times this looks like a dark abyss； at others, like the coming of first light.

name: Qurupeco Shard
description: A strong scale concealed by vivid plumage, grown to full maturity over many years.

name: Lustrous Feather
description: A vivid feather with an elegant luster. Qurupeco with these only live in certain regions.

name: Gobul Piel
description: Thick skin from a Gobul. Too rubbery for eating, but perfect for crafting equipment.

name: Gobul Surspike
description: An unusual barb from a Gobul. Only the most formidable of the breed have such precious spikes.

name: Arzuros Cortex
description: A superior Arzuros cortext. This highly-developed shell is a huge thorn in all hunters' sides.

name: Dazzling Fluid
description: A sparkling fluid with impressive water-retention ability. Improves performance and style.

name: Barroth Cortex
description: A Barroth's cortex. Years worth of mud have hardened it beyond all measure.

name: Barroth Crown
description: The heavy scalp of a formidable Barroth. As hard to remove as it is durable.

name: Volvidon Cortex
description: A heavy Volvidon cortext. Difficult to forge with, but can produce genuinely powerful gear.

name: Agnaktor Cortex
description: The rigid cortex of an Agnaktor. Highly heat-resistant, it produces bright red items when forged.

name: J.Barroth Cortex
description: The solid, ice-covered cortex of a Jade Barroth. The frosty coating is surprisngly strong.

name: Durambolite
description: A legendary gem rarely produced inside a Duramboros's body. Elegant, though gloomy.

name: Uragaan Cortex
description: An especially hard Uragaan cortex. Crafting with it can be a trying task, to say the least.

name: Uragaan Pallium
description: A legendary Uragaan shell. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

name: Nargacuga Mantle
description: A legendary Nargacuga scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

name: Lagiacrus Shard
description: The ultimate specimen of Lagiacrus Scale. Special skills are required to craft with it.

name: Deathly Shocker
description: A thick shell found on a select few Lagiacrus. It releases huge bolts of electricity.

name: Lagiacrus Mantle
description: A valuable azure scale found on select Lagiacrus. Said to greatly boost equipment performance.

name: I.Lagi D-Shocker
description: A thick shell seen only rarely on Ivory Lagiacrus. It can produce a veritable rain of thunderbolts.

name: I.Lagi Hardhorn
description: A fine horn from an Ivory Lagiacrus. Beloved by the rich for its flawless elegance.

name: S.Uragaan Scute+
description: A highly heat-resistant Steel Uragaan scute. Its rigidity makes it hard to use in forging.

name: Ceadeus Scale
description: Almost too large to be called a scale. Not as hard as you might think.

name: Deep Dragongem
description: One of the hardest materials to reap from a Ceadeus. Its center is a bottomless void.

name: Mohran Rockskin
description: A heavy shell piece taken from a Jhen Mohran. It surpasses even steel in strength.

name: Mohran Allbrace
description: A thick, high quality brace from a Jhen Mohran. Easy craftable with the right amount of force.

name: Deific Fang
description: A beautiful fang with a divine aura. Its shape and color best other Jhen Mohran fangs.

name: Cloudy Moonshard
description: The moon-like bladewing of a Lucent Nargacuga. He who crafts it controls the night.

name: Alatreon Mantle
description: The mantle of an Alatreon is the stuff of legend, containing traces of every element within.

name: A.Lagi D-Shocker
description: A thick shell from an Abyssal Lagiacrus's back. Turns the sea itself into an electrified weapon.

name: A.Lagi Dynamo
description: An unknown Abyssal Lagiacrus organ. Rumored to be the source of the monster's electricity.

name: Miralis Scale
description: A fiery black scale from a Dire Miralis. Also called the burning flower" for its eerie beauty."

name: Miralis Smelter
description: A burning hot core from a Dire Miralis's hips. A magma-like substance swirls inside it.

name: Dire Dragongem
description: A legendary gem expelled from the body of a Dire Miralis. It formed from crystallized magma.

name: Rustshard
description: A hunk of rock? No, it seems to be metal... With a little polish, it could be more.

name: Ancient Shard
description: A fossil? No, it seems to be metal... With a little polish, it could be more.

name: Rusted Fragment
description: A uniquely shaped metal fragment covered in rust. It looks like it could be used for something..

name: Map
description: A map of the hunting ground.

name: First-aid Med
description: Restores a tiny bit of Health. It does a body... sort of good!

name: Ration
description: Slightly boosts current/max Stamina. Most hunters agree: it's gross.

name: Portable Spit
description: A Guild-provided BBQ Spit useful for novice hunters.

name: Mini Whetstone
description: A portable Whetstone you can use to restore Sharpness to weapons.

name: EZ Shock Trap
description: Immobilizes a target for easy capture.

name: EZ Flash Bomb
description: A grenade-like bomb that flashes brightly on impact.

name: EZ Barrel Bomb L
description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb L (as potent as a B. Bomb L+). OK underwater.

name: Ballista Ammo
description: Ammunition for a large mounted Bowgun.

name: Ballista Binder
description: Ammunition for a large mounted Bowgun. Keep giants from moving!

name: Cannon Ammo
description: Special ammunition for an anti-dragon cannon. Not fun to lug around.

name: Anti-dragon Bomb
description: A small time bomb that sticks to targets.

name: Torch
description: Use this to light up dark places and stave off certain monsters.

name: Paw Pass Ticket
description: Deliver to end the Quest. Maybe the Felynes will take you home...

name: Unique Mushroom
description: A pinky-sized mushroom valued for its unusual aroma.

name: Choice Mushroom
description: The perfect shape and aroma. Even better than a Unique Mushroom.

name: Ripened Mushroom
description: A unique Mushroom made more unique by maturing its aroma and flavor.

name: Goldenfish
description: A rare fish made of solid gold. Sell it for a tidy sum.

name: Royal Rhino
description: A beetle with a jewel-like gleam. Prized by bug fans of all ages.

name: Crystal Bone
description: A unique bone prized in the village for reasons unknown.

name: Bloodstone
description: Is this crimson stone the relic of some ancient beast?

name: Monster Guts
description: Monster innards galore. A prized delicacy.

name: Popo Tongue
description: Popo Tongue are popular, healthy, and fun to eat.

name: Wyvern Egg
description: An egg taken from a flying wyvern's nest. Very fragile, so handle with care.

name: Herbivore Egg
description: An egg stolen from an herbivore's nest. It looks pretty tasty.

name: Powderstone
description: A rock that explodes with even the slightest jolt. Careful!

name: Wyvern Tear
description: Mysterious tears wept only on special occasions.

name: Pinnacle Coin
description: A glorious coin given only to unquestioned Masters of Hunting. Beyond priceless.

name: Hunter King Coin
description: A silver coin given only to True Hunters. Its gleam is a symbol of your glory.

name: Beast Coin
description: An award granted for defeating a fanged beast in the Arena. A sharp fang is carved on it.

name: Flying Coin
description: An award granted for defeating a flying wyvern in the Arena. Proof one challenged the skies.

name: Voucher
description: Redeem this for a special meal with stronger effects than usual.

name: Gourmet Voucher
description: Exchange this for a kingly meal. Both its flavor and effects are top notch.

name: Commendation
description: A ticket awarded for a display of bravery. Collect enough and it might pay off.

name: Conqueror's Seal
description: Proof you have overcome countless trials, and a true badge of honor.

name: Pawprint Stamp
description: Lynain paper currency, stamped with a pawprint. The letters written on it are unfamiliar.

name: VE Ticket
description: A ticket awarded in recognition of contributions to the Guild. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

name: VE Deluxe Ticket
description: A ticket awarded in recognition of contributions to the Guild. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

name: VE Bronze Ticket
description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

name: VE Silver Ticket
description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. The Veggie Elder may offer a rare trade...

name: VE Cosmic Ticket
description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. The Veggie Elder may offer an amazing trade...

name: Steel Egg
description: A egg of glittering steel. Very valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

name: Silver Egg
description: A egg of glittering silver. Very valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

name: Golden Egg
description: An egg of glittering gold. Insanely valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

name: Aquaglow Jewel
description: An indispensible item used in Decorations.

name: Sunspire Jewel
description: An indispensible item used in Decorations.

name: Bloodrun Jewel
description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. A shame that these are so high-end.

name: Lazurite Jewel
description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. This one doesn't come along often.

name: Adamant Orb
description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. A rare orb that houses immense power.
